description: Why is it that some people seem to be able to build muscle much faster than others? Most say that genetics, diet, and lifting time are the factors that dictate how much muscle you can put on. This is not the case. It is true that those things affect your ability, but the number 1 reason why some people can gain muscle faster is their workout and exercise regime. The type of lifts you do and the ratio of reps to weight impact your ability to gain muscle far more than your genetics. Stop wasting your time and start training for results. Download the Body Building Secrets Revealed ebook today!
